    "help_title": "ChordReference Help",
    "help_section1": "1. Chord And Key View\n   - The T/S/D cards show tonic, subdominant, dominant chords and extensions.\n   - Click an empty area on a card to audition the chord.\n   - Card tools: inversion, rhythm, and MIDI drag export.\n   - The top bar allows MIDI device selection, audition mode, and key lock.",
    "help_section2": "2. Circle Of Fifths\n   - Click the outer major ring or inner minor ring to change key.\n   - Left-click the center dice to generate a TSD progression; right-click to choose style.\n   - The top scale selector supports major, minor, and modal scales.",
    "help_section3": "3. MIDI Input\n   - Select a MIDI input device from the top bar.\n   - Lock Key keeps the current key and only updates chord function.",
    "help_section4": "4. Preset Browser\n   - Use the left sidebar for categories, Favorites, Frequent, and User Presets.\n   - Right-click a preset to favorite it, mark it frequent, edit, or delete user presets.\n   - Shift-click supports multi-select for batch export/delete.\n   - Import/Export buttons support single JSON or ZIP packages.",
    "help_section5": "5. Negative Harmony\n   - Toggle Negative Harmony from the top bar.\n   - Audition and MIDI drag use the displayed harmony.",
    "help_section6": "6. Shortcuts\n   - F1 or ?: Help\n   - P: Open/close Preset Browser\n   - S: Switch skin\n   - L: Toggle Lock Key\n   - N: Toggle Negative Harmony\n   - M: Toggle MIDI Out\n   - In Preset Browser: Space play/stop, Left/Right switch preset, Esc close\n   - In main view: Click card to audition, drag MIDI icon to DAW track.",
    "help_section7": "7. Data Storage\n   - User presets are stored in the ChordReference UserPresets folder.\n   - Favorites use favorites.json; frequent presets use frequent.json.\n   - Factory presets are re-extracted on each startup to ensure updates.",

